@node Introduktion "What's this WWSpell for?"


                            INTRODUCTION


Are you one of those who don't have English as your native language?

Do you misspell a lot of documents?

Are you using WordWorth 6?


If you answered Yes! to all these questions, you just can't live 
without this script!!!

WWSpell uses the program AlphaSpell to spellcheck a document through
Wordworth's arexxport. It's pretty slow, but it's a great help if 
you press the wrong keys once in a while :^) 



@endnode

@node Krav "Needs to run WWSpell"


                             Requirements


To be able to use WWSpell you'll need:

* An amiga :)
* Wordworth 6+ (older versions might work too, I haven't tried)
* Arexx must be active with RexxMast (Sys:System/)
* Alphaspell (text/edit aspell.lha)
* A dictionary in your language (text/edit 'your language'.lha)  
* A harddrive would be nice...

@endnode

@node Installation "Installation"


                            INSTALLATION


1. Install ASpell using the installer.

2. Install your language dictionary with the other dictionarys.

3. Copy WWSpell.rexx to WordWorth6/WWRexx/

4. Copy this GuideFile wherever you want it... (except ram:)  :^)

5. In WordWorth: Choose 'Arexx Macros' in the 'Tools' menu.

6. Click 'add' and choose 'WWSpell.rexx' 

7. Click 'Ok' (unless you doubleclicked already..)

8. Save your Settings in the 'Settings' menu.

9. Open WWspell with a ordinary text-editor (ed, ced, GoldED)

10. Change these lines to your configuration:


/* !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Your Personal Settings !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! */

language='Swedish'                      The name of your language
alphaspelldrawer='c:'                   The drawer where Alphaspell is
dictionarydrawer='work:ord/misc/dict/'  Your dictionary drawer

/* !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! */


WARNING!: DONT REMOVE THE QUOTES!!!


11. Send a 060-card to me!!! :^)


@endnode

@node Användning "How to use WWSpell"


                               USAGE


Choose 'Arrex macros' from the 'Tools' menu. Click on 'WWSpell.rexx'
and 'Play'. The script will now copy the Dictionaries, AlphaSpell
and 'delete' to 'RAM:Spell/' (these files will be removed from 'RAM:'
when the script finishes). 

The Script will now go through the words one by one. If it finds a 
word that isn't in the dictionaries, it will show a requester:

 ----------------------------------------
| WWSpell request                        |
|                                        |
| Word wasn't found in the dictionary.   |
|                                        |
| Change: Word                           |
|                                        |
| ------     ------    ------     -----  |
| Ignore     Change    Learn      Abort  |
 ----------------------------------------

'Ignore' Moves to the next word without changing anything.

'Change' Changes the word to the one written in the textbox.

'Learn'  Adds the word IN THE TEXTBOX to the userdictionary.

'Abort'  Exits the script. 



@endnode

